# рЯУЯ SH1106 OLED Display with Arduino

> This example demonstrates how to display two lines of text on a **1.3" SH1106 I2C OLED display** using the **U8g2** library.

---

# рЯУВ Required Libraries

| рЯУЪ Library | рЯУЭ Description |
|:-----------|:---------------|
| `Arduino.h` | Provides the core Arduino functions. |
| `U8g2lib.h` | Controls the SH1106 OLED display. |
| `Wire.h` | Enables I2C communication. |

```cpp
#include <Arduino.h>
#include <U8g2lib.h>
#include <Wire.h>
```

---

# рЯЦ•пЄП Creating the OLED Object

```cpp
U8G2_SH1106_128X64_NONAME_F_HW_I2C u8g2(
    U8G2_R0,
    /* reset=*/ U8X8_PIN_NONE
);
```

## Description

| Parameter | Description |
|:----------|:------------|
| `U8G2_SH1106_128X64_NONAME_F_HW_I2C` | SH1106 OLED driver for a 128√Ч64 display |
| `U8G2_R0` | No screen rotation (0¬∞ orientation) |
| `U8X8_PIN_NONE` | No reset pin is used |

---

# вЪЩпЄП setup()

```cpp
void setup()
{
    u8g2.begin();
    u8g2.enableUTF8Print();
}
```

## рЯФє `u8g2.begin();`

Initializes the OLED display.

- вЬЕ Starts I2C communication.
- вЬЕ Allocates the display buffer.
- вЬЕ Prepares the display for use.

---

## рЯФє `u8g2.enableUTF8Print();`

Enables UTF-8 character support.

This allows special characters such as:

```text
√З  ƒЮ  ƒ∞  √Ц  ≈Ю  √Ь
```

to be displayed correctly.

---

# рЯФД loop()

```cpp
void loop()
{
    u8g2.clearBuffer();

    u8g2.setFont(u8g2_font_ncenB14_tr);

    u8g2.setCursor(0,24);
    u8g2.print("Huseyin");

    u8g2.setCursor(0,50);
    u8g2.print("ERDEM");

    u8g2.sendBuffer();

    delay(1000);
}
```

---

# рЯІє clearBuffer()

```cpp
u8g2.clearBuffer();
```

Clears the **display buffer** stored in memory.

> The physical OLED screen is **not updated immediately**. Only the buffer is cleared.

---

# рЯФ§ setFont()

```cpp
u8g2.setFont(u8g2_font_ncenB14_tr);
```

Selects the font used for drawing text.

Features of this font:

- Supports Turkish characters
- Bold style
- Approximately **14 pixels** high

---

# рЯУН setCursor()

```cpp
u8g2.setCursor(x, y);
```

Sets the starting position of the text.

| Parameter | Description |
|:----------|:------------|
| `x` | Horizontal position |
| `y` | Vertical position |

### First Line

```cpp
